714582f-a.title: Manhattan: 79th Street (West) - Columbus Avenue
714582f-a.text:
121 (four story) and 123 West 79th Street, north side, west of Columbus Avenue (right, not seenl, showing at the first listed address, the home of Hozea Seki, who, with his wife has been conducting Buddhist services here for nearly a year. According to the New York Times of June 3, 1938, the New York Buddhist Church has accuired the four story building at No. 171 West 94th Street, and will convert same for religious purposes and thereby establish the first Buddhist Church in the east of this country. For a photograph of this structure, see files under that address.
May 9, 1938
George D. Chinn
